</content></a></div></div>Transportation to/from the airport:</div></h3><p id="h.p_ojOKoEN_ypf1" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">The closest major airport is the <a class="dhtgD" href="http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.metroairport.com%2F&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNEJhG5GUNyobwwsilYNIicSaccSIw" target="_blank">Detroit Metropolitan Wayne County Airport (DTW)</a>. There are several options for transportation to/from DTW. We recommend the following:</p><p id="h.p_mTK1Wgiiypf4" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;"><em><strong>Metro cab</strong></em> (taxi service - available at DTW)</p><p id="h.p__oU-g7HcyvcT" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">website: <a class="dhtgD" href="http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.metroairportcabs.com%2F&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNENCM3bNzJbxpScA4x9-jRktsexgg" target="_blank">http://www.metroairportcabs.com/</a></p><p id="h.p_aBjo2ozxyvcV" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">phone: (800) 505-3161</p><p id="h.p_MMpmRgl3Mqit" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">cost: ~$70 + tip</p><p id="h.p_xQqy2I60yvcX" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;"><em><strong>Lyft</strong></em> or <em><strong>Uber</strong></em> (app-based transportation services)</p><p id="h.p_-gd4cTi4yvcY" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">website: <a class="dhtgD" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lyft.com%2F&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNH3_v_aGA7ezjgfYeGdCgF-CwLGgw" target="_blank">https://www.lyft.com/</a> or <a class="dhtgD" href="https://www.google.com/url?q=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uber.com%2F&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNEmqC1g_PSSyZCgQSC-VqLtBuFIUA" target="_blank">https://www.uber.com/</a></p><p id="h.p_OV96BrE1yvcb" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">Both Lyft and Uber are app-based transportation services. To use either of them, you need to first download the app onto your smartphone. The apps are available free to download from both the Apple App store and the Google Play store.</p><p id="h.p_PB1VasQ8MsTb" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">cost: ~$40</p><p id="h.p_3Era2jory2tx" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;"><em><strong>Michigan Flyer</strong></em> (bus service)</p><p id="h.p__if7jlP5y25y" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">website: <a class="dhtgD" href="http://www.google.com/url?q=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.michiganflyer.com%2F&amp;sa=D&amp;sntz=1&amp;usg=AFQjCNEYpIq3CQa_CnjLpR1381VmtRnaPQ" target="_blank">http://www.michiganflyer.com/</a></p><p id="h.p_I7qWdqyQLIaE" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">cost: $12/$15 one way (advance purchase / on board), $22 roundtrip</p><p id="h.p_ohLPk1KvM2Pc" class="zfr3Q" style="text-align: left;">Advance purchase tickets for the Flyer have to be booked on the website at least 1 hour in advance of the desired travel date/time. Note that there are two stops in Ann Arbor, so depending on where your hotel is, one might be preferable to the other.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div><div class="Xpil1b"></div><footer class="BCtCv" jscontroller="HSKGsf" jsaction="rcuQ6b:WYd;" data-create-site-url="https://sites.google.com/new/?authuser=0&amp;usp=viewer_footer&amp;authuser=0"><div class="uByue"><div class="yYF4Mc"><div><div class="qmpcfe">